						               													<description>Factory Floor is a light weight, polyomino (tetris-tiles) placement board game for 1-4 players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As a fresh faced factory builder your tasked with building the most productive facility using the limited space provided in the most effective way possible. Using production facilities and quality control to increase the overall output of the factory, further increases to your output is made by the hiring and allocation of workers&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player starts a with a floor space of 12x8 which can be make more difficult with the inclusion of column pieces. Each then takes turns selecting tiles or hiring workers to make the very most of their floor space and labor pool&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After 5 production phases, and just one work week, the player who has managed to create the greatest output is named the manufacturing mogul supreme.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Factory Floor also provides an extensive single player campaign of 15 scenarios as players attempt to successfully carry out the wishes of the local county council of Cogspinham.  Can you revitalize this production powerhouse or is the town going to be left spinning.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
